  "prompt": "What are the different types of agriculture and how are they practiced?",
  "response": "There are several types of agriculture, each with unique characteristics and practices:\n\n1. Subsistence Agriculture\n- Small-scale farming\n- Primarily producing food for family/local consumption\n- Limited technology and resources\n- Common in developing countries\n\n2. Commercial Agriculture\n- Large-scale farming\n- Produces crops and livestock for market sale\n- Uses advanced technology and machinery\n- Focuses on maximizing productivity and profit\n\n3. Intensive Agriculture\n- High input of labor and capital\n- Maximizes land productivity\n- Uses fertilizers, pesticides, and advanced techniques\n- Higher crop yields per acre\n\n4. Extensive Agriculture\n- Large land areas with minimal labor\n- Lower input of resources\n- Lower crop yields\n- Common in regions with abundant land\n\n5. Organic Agriculture\n- No synthetic chemicals or pesticides\n- Focuses on environmental sustainability\n- Uses natural fertilizers and pest control methods\n- Emphasizes soil health\n\n6. Plantation Agriculture\n- Large estates growing single crop\n- Typically in tropical/subtropical regions\n- Crops like tea, coffee, rubber, sugarcane\n- Often export-oriented\n\n7. Vertical Farming\n- Crops grown in vertically stacked layers\n- Indoor controlled environments\n- Uses hydroponic or aeroponic techniques\n- Maximizes space and reduces water usage\n\nEach type has specific advantages and challenges based on environmental, economic, and social contexts.",
